As part of his quest towards improving a better conducive environment for effective teaching and learning, Abdullahi Adamu Bazuwa, a member representing Potiskum Central at the Yobe State House of Assembly has facilitated the construction of 18 classrooms and 20 Toilets in Sabon Layi Primary School in Potiskum town. The lawmaker’s delegation witnessed the handing over ceremony of the project by the contractor. The school management and the host community applauded his efforts for facilitating such multi-million naira projects to the community. The contractor and the community members emphasized the need for proper maintenance, sustainability and security of the project for long term benefits. Osun PDP Crisis: Lawmaker Seeks Elder Caucus’ Intervention NASS To Support Carbonated Drinks Tax Law, Says, Lawmaker The contractor who handed over the project to SDGs, the lawmaker received and handed over the project to the State Universal Basic Education Board (SUBEB). The lawmaker Bazuwa used the forum to appreciate Yobe State Governor Mai Mala Buni for his unflinching support towards citizens of Potiskum, “Governor Buni’s love and passion for education is yielding a positive result across the state and on behalf of my constituents I say, a big thank you, your Excellency Sir”. “Finally, thanks to the Coordinator SDGs Yobe State Arch. Musa Sule Damagum and his team, we thank you for such a huge and yet very important project in our community. Thanks to the friendly contractor for putting in such qualitative work and in time, thank you and God bless you all”.